  "fields": {
    "apply_url": "https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/deliveroo/40eda86c-88e7-4220-94cf-b84a6c4133c1/application",
    "company": "Deliveroo",
    "compensation": "",
    "content_hash": "2476d825a713ddbb",
    "department": "Deliveroo Cost Center Hierarchy",
    "description": "Strategy \u0026 Planning Manager\n\nAs a Strategic Planning Manager, you will lead the strategic planning function for deliveroo’s merchant team. This is a high-impact role that defines our annual strategic plans, ensures strategic priorities are translated into actionable plans and targets, and tracked effectively. You will be the key strategic partner to the merchant leadership and a wide range of cross-functional teams, including Commercial, Product, Finance, Marketing, and Data Science. This role reports into the Mx Strategy Director.\n\nThis role requires excellent planning and project management skills paired with strong commercial acumen. We are looking for someone who can work at the most senior level, juggle multiple complex projects, motivate senior stakeholders and cut through detail to craft a sharp narrative.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n\n - Annual and Quarterly Planning: Own and run the Merchant org’s annual and quarterly planning cycles. You’ll work with senior leaders to turn high-level strategy into clear plans and ensure resources are allocated to the right priorities.\n\n - Target Setting \u0026 Tracking: Lead the target-setting process from start to finish. You’ll build and manage the tracking systems and reporting that keep everyone accountable for hitting OKRs and business goals.\n\n - Reporting: Be the primary voice for reporting progress on the Mx strategy. You’ll translate complex updates into clear, concise narratives for the wider company and weekly updates for the Executive team.\n\n - Strategic Project Oversight: Take full responsibility for key strategic projects. This means getting stakeholders aligned, resolving blockages, and making sure the roll-out to frontline teams is a success.\n\n - Support for Pods: Provide hands-on support to our cross-functional teams (\"Pods\"). You’ll manage their ways of working, align on their templates and meeting processes, and act as the bridge between them and the global market leadership teams.\n\n - Ways of Working: Take the lead on how the merchant leadership team and their teams operate to achieve strategic targets. You will own the structure and content of monthly area reviews to ensure these meetings stay productive and focused.\n\n - Leadership Team Processes: Build and manage the day-to-day processes that help the leadership team stay organized, make decisions quickly, and keep information flowing smoothly across the business.\n\n - Operational Excellence: Set and maintain a high bar for how the team works. You’ll ensure our processes are simple, repeatable, and actually help the business hit its objectives rather than adding unnecessary friction.\n\nAbout You\n\n - 6+ years of experience in consulting, strategy, chief of staff, business operations, or product operations; in a fast moving environment\n\n - Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal, with the ability to influence across teams and Exec level leadership\n\n - Demonstrated ability to drive structure, clarity and impact in complex environments\n\n - Strong commercial acumen and ability to balance tight deadlines with managing the impact on our frontline teams and merchant partners\n\n - High personal ownership and bias for action, while knowing when to escalate or seek alignment\n\n - Collaborative mindset, able to work across a diverse set of teams and perspectives\n\n - (Bonus) Experience in marketplaces, consumer tech, food delivery or multi-market businesses\n\nWhy Join Us?\n\nAt Deliveroo, you’ll do work that matters, solving real-world problems in a three-sided marketplace that’s constantly evolving. We’re food lovers, problem solvers, community builders and more, brought together by a shared drive to make things better. Working here you can expect to:\n\n - 🔧 Make a visible impact every day – Your work directly improves experiences for customers, partners and riders.\n\n - 🌱 Learn fast in an entrepreneurial environment – Work close to the market with autonomy, pace and real responsibility.\n\n - 🧠 Build a career, not just a role – Stretch yourself, develop new skills and grow as the business evolves.\n\n - 🌎 Deliver together in an inclusive culture – Collaborative, values-driven teams that support how you work best.\n\nWe aim to create a fair process that lets your skills shine—our interview typically includes 3-4 stages. Find more about how we hire here https://careers.deliveroo.co.uk/how-we-hire/.\n\nOur Global Structure\n\nDeliveroo is now part of DoorDash, bringing together teams with even greater reach, scale, and ambition. Depending on your role, you may collaborate with teammates, systems, and leaders across DoorDash and Wolt. Together, we’re unlocking new possibilities as one global team.\n\nDiversity, Equity and Inclusion\n\nAt Deliveroo, we know that a great workplace reflects the world around us and that true diversity and inclusion make us stronger, more creative, and better at what we do. We’re committed to fostering an environment where everyone can do their best work and feel they belong.\n\nWe believe in equality of opportunity and welcome candidates from all backgrounds regardless of age, gender, ethnicity, disability, sexual orientation, gender identity, socio-economic background, religion, or belief.\n\nIf you have a disability or long-term health condition and need support to apply for one of our roles, or require any reasonable adjustments during the recruitment process, you’ll have the opportunity to let us know once you’ve submitted your application. We’ll share details on how to request support so we can ensure you have a fair and equitable experience.\n\nIf you’re excited about making a real impact in a fast-moving marketplace and growing your career alongside ambitious, supportive teams, we’d love to hear from you!",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
